Aneta Chepinska.-Born in Poland,with Polish women regarded as smart ,and self-assured.Aneta having that Beautiful DNA ,drama,and intensity to succeed.Aneta has always been intriqued by the beauty/cosmetic Field and curious to research what's new and hot on the market.This path led Aneta to becoming that ultimate skin care professional.
Aneta attended The Florida College of Natural Health,a member of The Steiner Education Group(SEG),which operates massage therapy schools and skin care schools at 31 campuses in 14 states.Steiner Education  Group is a subsidiary of Steiner Leisure Limited ,which operates more than 200 spas on cruise ships and resorts worldwide.
Aneta completed her degree and received her diploma from The LEADER IN SKIN HEALTH EDUCATION,leading to this exciting career in Paramedical Skin Care.The diploma program includes the entire Skin Care Training Program .The courses provided integrated training in both clinical and holistic skin care.Aneta has completed the most advanced skin care training marketable,Aneta has been with all skin care theory and techniques.Aneta's responsibilities include;analyzing skin types and conditions,develop therapeutic skin care programs for specific skin types and conditions,explain treatment protocols and explain possible side effects,educate clients, and advise clients on home -care programs and products.Most importantly for success and a satisfied client is to communicate clearly and effectively ,skills that will not be compromised.This is a time of revolutionary change in what we know about the skin and the ways we care for it.Keeping the skin healthy and youthful looking for decades is no longer just a fantasy.Surrounding Aneta is a T.E.A.M, Where Together Everyone Achieves More.
PCA skin Certified practice, Licensed.
